definition.value: A branched amino octasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 6 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man group and at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-[beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man group.
An amino disaccharide consisting of 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-beta-D-glucopyranose residue and a 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-D-galactopyranose residue joined in sequence by a (1->3) glycosidic bond.
A beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-L-Araf in which the carbon bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha configuration.
